criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Primary single hepatocellular carcinoma confirmed by histology or cytology, with a
             maximum diameter ≤5.0 cm;

               -  Good liver function, Child-Pugh grade A;

                    -  No serious dysfunction of heart, lung, kidney and other important organs ④
                       Liver resection or radiofrequency ablation was performed in our hospital,
                       and the study protocol and follow-up procedure were followed.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who cannot perform DCE-MRI examination due to metal implants in the body ②
             Patients who had received other treatment before DCE-MRI or CEUS;

               -  Invisible lesions, diffuse lesions or poor DCE-MRI/CEUS image quality under CEUS;
                  ④ Drug abuse, clinical or psychological or social factors that make informed
                  consent or study implementation affected.
